author: Zonebourse
title: L'entreprise indienne Jakson Green se rapproche d'une levée de fonds de 476 millions de dollars pour accroître sa capacité en matière d'énergies renouvelables - Zonebourse
text:
L'entreprise indienne Jakson Green se rapproche d'une levée de fonds de plus de 40 milliards de roupies (476,4 millions de dollars) afin d'accroître sa capacité en matière d'énergies renouvelables, a déclaré le directeur général conjoint Krishnan Kannan. L'entreprise privée, qui dispose actuellement d'une capacité installée d'environ 250 mégawatts, ajoutera 1 gigawatt (GW) d'ici le début de 2026.
"Nous travaillons avec un partenaire stratégique pour apporter l'investissement. Pour ce 1 GW, l'investissement sera d'environ 40 milliards de roupies, réparti entre 75 % de dettes et 25 % de capitaux propres", a déclaré M. Kannan à Reuters jeudi, en marge de l'exposition Renewable Energy India Expo, à New Delhi.
L'entreprise est en pourparlers avancés avec des fonds d'énergie verte et vise à clôturer la levée de fonds d'ici novembre, a-t-il ajouté.
L'entreprise fait partie du groupe Jakson, qui est également présent dans la fabrication de modules et de cellules solaires par le biais d'une autre unité appelée Jakson Solar.
Un nombre croissant d'entreprises indiennes développent leur capacité en matière d'énergies renouvelables et lèvent des fonds, le gouvernement ayant pour objectif d'ajouter au moins 500 GW d'énergie propre d'ici à 2030 afin de réduire les émissions de gaz à effet de serre.
Jakson Green cherche également à augmenter sa capacité de production d'énergie renouvelable de 1 GW par an au cours des cinq prochaines années et lèvera des fonds en fonction de ses besoins, a déclaré M. Kannan.
Jakson Green a remporté plus de 1 GW de projets d'énergie renouvelable auprès du gouvernement indien, notamment auprès de Solar Energy Corporation of India et de NHPC, et a obtenu en juillet une facilité de crédit de la First Abu Dhabi Bank pour son expansion internationale.
En septembre, la société a signé un accord avec le prêteur d'infrastructure indien REC pour un montant de 14,2 milliards de roupies afin de financer les projets d'énergie de Jakson.
(1 $ = 83,9630 roupies indiennes)

author: Redacción
title: Barcelona SC y Emelec, entre los 10 clubes que apoyan la creación de la serie C
text:
Por medio de una carta dirigida a la Federación Ecuatoriana de Fútbol (FEF) diez clubes del fútbol ecuatoriano pujan por la creación de la serie C en el próximo congreso ordinario a celebrarse el 31 de enero en Quito.
Barcelona SC, Emelec, Independiente del Valle, El Nacional, Orense, Técnico Universitario, Independiente Jrs., Guayaquil City, Leones del Norte y Nueve de Octubre son los clubes que firmaron la misiva.
‘Otra vez, por odio y ego, no se hacen las cosas’, la respuesta de Miguel Ángel Loor ante la negativa de la FEF a la creación de la serie CTajante rechazo de la Ecuafútbol a la serie C: ‘No, señores, yo a la Federación la voy a hacer respetar’, dice el presidente Francisco Egas
En ella, se propone que se analice esta propuesta para que esta posible nueva categoría fomente el desarrollo de más equipos y jugadores en el país, además que podría servir como el regreso de varios clubes históricos.
Publicidad
“Hoy en día existe una problemática histórica en los torneos de segunda categoría, con una falta de recursos, principalmente; a veces no se tienen ni para los balones. Por consiguiente, cuando un equipo desciende a la serie B, ir a esta actual segunda categoría prácticamente uno desaparece como club profesional”, se lee en la misiva.
Leones del Norte y los ciudadanos son los dos conjuntos que surgieron con la idea de redactar la carta hacia el máximo ente del balompié ecuatoriano.
En las últimas semanas, la idea de este proyecto ha causado tensión entre la FEF y la Liga Pro, principalmente entre sus presidentes, Francisco Egas y Miguel Ángel Loor, respectivamente.
Publicidad
En redes sociales, se viralizó un audio de Egas en el que afirmaba que no se dejaría “imponer” por nadie esta iniciativa. Inmediatamente, Loor le respondió, bastante molesto, que nuevamente las cosas no se realizarán “por odio y ego”. (D)

author: CA
title: Antibes: un ado de 16 ans qui projetait une tuerie de masse dans un lycée mis en examen et écroué
text:
Un adolescent de 16 ans, soupçonné de préparer une tuerie de masse à Antibes, vient d'être mis en examen et placé en détention. Ce lycéen souffre de troubles psychiatriques. Sa petite amie de 17 ans, elle aussi hospitalisée en psychiatrie, a été placée en garde-à-vue. Un adolescent de 16 ans, habitant Antibes (Alpes-Maritimes) et présentant des troubles psychiatriques, a été mis en examen et écroué, soupçonné d'avoir nourri un projet de "tuerie de masse sans connotation religieuse", a annoncé jeudi 25 avril le parquet de Grasse dans un communiqué.
Le Conseil départemental des Alpes-Maritimes avait fait un signalement à la justice en février, car l'adolescent, de nationalité turque, avait tenu des propos inquiétants à son pédopsychiatre. Dans la foulée, le parquet ouvrait une enquête, mais les premières investigations avaient conduit à une hospitalisation d'office du suspect.
Des croix gammées dans sa chambre Les investigations ont permis de "confirmer que le jeune homme nourrissait un projet de tuerie de masse, sans connotation religieuse", écrit le parquet. Le parquet national antiterroriste a été avisé, mais la juridiction grassoise reste pour le moment saisie des faits.
Lors d'une perquisition au domicile du suspect à Antibes, les enquêteurs de la police judiciaire, qui ont récupéré le dossier après l'ouverture d'une information judiciaire, ont découvert "des croix gammées et de signes cabalistiques sur les murs de sa chambre". Ils ont également saisi "des carnets décrivant à grands traits son projet criminel, des armes blanches et un gilet tactique pare-balle".
À sa sortie de l'hôpital, l'adolescent a donc été placé en garde à vue. Et mercredi, à l'issue de son audition, il a été mis en examen des chefs de participation à une association de malfaiteurs en vue de la préparation d'un crime, en l'espèce des assassinats, et d'apologie publique de crime ou délit.
Une jeune femme placé en garde à vue "L'instruction se poursuit et permettra notamment d'apprécier la responsabilité pénale du mineur au vu des troubles psychiatriques qu'il présente", insiste le parquet. Par ailleurs, une autre adolescente, âgée de 17 ans et demeurant à l'autre bout de la France, dans la Manche, a également été placée en garde à vue.
L'exploitation de l'ordinateur et du téléphone du jeune antibois "a révélé qu'il était entré contact" avec elle alors qu'elle était "hospitalisée en psychiatrie à Cherbourg-en-Cotentin" et "semblait partager ses intentions meurtrières". Elle a été hospitalisée sans consentement à l'issue de sa garde à vue.

author: Tomas Meskauskas
title: Freshfruittab.com Redirect
text:
How to remove freshfruittab.com from the settings of a browser
 Written by Tomas Meskauskas on
What is freshfruittab.com?
We have inspected freshfruittab.com and found it to be a fake search engine. We also discovered that freshfruittab.com is promoted through a [browser hijacker](/common-types-of-computer-infections#browser-hijacker), an extension called Fresh Fruit Search. Fake search engines and browser hijackers should be avoided. Thus, if freshfruittab.com and Fresh Fruit Search are present on browsers, they should be removed.
Freshfruittab.com and Fresh Fruit Search overview
Freshfruittab.com is a fake search engine because it does not generate results. Instead, when a search query using a hijacked browser is entered, freshfruittab.com [redirects to bing.com](/removal-guides/9633-bing-com-redirect). It is worth noting that bing.com is a legitimate search engine. However, freshfruittab.com should not be trusted.
Fake search engines like freshfruittab.com can promote shady websites, including unreliable search engines. Users may be exposed to phishing sites, various scams, malware, and other threats. Using fake search engines might result in privacy and security risks, as well as other issues like monetary loss.
Furhermore, freshfruittab.com is promoted via a browser hijacker, Fresh Fruit Search. This extension forces users to visit freshfruittab.com by making it the default search engine, homepage, and new tab page. It is likely that freshfruittab.com cannot be removed from a web browser while Fresh Fruit Search is added.
It is also important to note that Fresh Fruit Search can access and alter any data on freshfruittab.com, potentially stealing personal information or introducing harmful changes. The extension can also block content on any webpage, potentially preventing users from viewing certain elements or navigating the site properly.
Therefore, it is strongly advisable to avoid adding Fresh Fruit Search to browsers and remove the extension (and freshfruittab.com) if it is already present.

Conclusion
In conclusion, it is important to be careful when encountering suspicious websites (fake search engines) and browser hijackers. These threats can expose users to various risks, including malware, privacy breaches, and financial loss. More examples of fake search engines are [search-thrill.com](/removal-guides/31882-search-thrill-com-redirect), [topgreenview.com](/removal-guides/31846-topgreenview-com-redirect), and [search-great.com](/removal-guides/31841-search-great-com-redirect).
How did Fresh Fruit Search hijacked my browser?
Browser hijackers are often bundled with other (mostly free or suspicious) programs. They hijack browsers when users finish installations without deselecting them. Usually, unwanted offers are hidden in "Advanced", "Custom", or similar settings during installations or mentioned near ticked checkboxes.
Furthermore, browser hijacking can occur through deceptive advertisements, fake updates, notifications from shady sites, and similar channels. Users may also end up having their browsers hijacked through downloads from unofficial pages or app stores, P2P networks, third-party downloaders, etc.
How to avoid installation of browser hijackers?
Always download software, extensions, and apps from official websites or reputable app stores. Avoid third-party sources. During software installations, choose "Custom" or "Advanced" options to spot and reject any unwanted apps or extensions. Do not click links in suspicious emails or messages, and avoid interacting with ads and similar elements on questionable pages.
Never permit shady websites to send you notifications. Keep the operating system (and installed programs) up to date, and use a reliable security tool. If your computer is already infected with Fresh Fruit Search, we recommend running a scan with [Combo Cleaner Antivirus for Windows](/download-combo-cleaner-windows) to automatically eliminate this browser hijacker.

Fresh Fruit Search browser hijacker removal:
Windows 11 users:
Right-click on the Start icon, select Apps and Features. In the opened window search for the application you want to uninstall, after locating it, click on the three vertical dots and select Uninstall.
Windows 10 users:
Right-click in the lower left corner of the screen, in the Quick Access Menu select Control Panel. In the opened window choose Programs and Features.
Windows 7 users:
Click Start (Windows Logo at the bottom left corner of your desktop), choose Control Panel. Locate Programs and click Uninstall a program.
macOS (OSX) users:
Click Finder, in the opened screen select Applications. Drag the app from the Applications folder to the Trash (located in your Dock), then right click the Trash icon and select Empty Trash.
In the uninstall programs window: look for any recently installed suspicious applications, select these entries and click "Uninstall" or "Remove".
After uninstalling the potentially unwanted applications (which cause browser redirects to the freshfruittab.com website), scan your computer for any remaining unwanted components. To scan your computer, use [recommended malware removal software](/top-antivirus).
Fresh Fruit Search browser hijacker removal from Internet browsers:
Video showing how to remove browser redirects:
Remove malicious extensions from Google Chrome:
Click the Chrome menu icon (at the top right corner of Google Chrome), select "Extensions" and click "Manage Extensions". Locate "Fresh Fruit Search" and other recently-installed suspicious extensions, select these entries and click "Remove".
Change your homepage:
Click the Chrome menu icon (at the top right corner of Google Chrome), select "Settings". In the "On startup" section, disable "Fresh Fruit Search", look for a browser hijacker URL (hxxp://www.freshfruittab.com) below the "Open a specific or set of pages" option. If present click on the three vertical dots icon and select "Remove".
Change your default search engine:
To change your default search engine in Google Chrome: Click the Chrome menu icon (at the top right corner of Google Chrome), select "Settings", in the "Search engine" section, click "Manage search engines...", in the opened list look for "freshfruittab.com", when located click the three vertical dots near this URL and select "Delete".
- If you continue to have problems with browser redirects and unwanted advertisements -
[Reset Google Chrome](/how-to-remove-spyware/reset-browser-settings#chrome).
Optional method:
If you continue to have problems with removal of the fruit search browser hijacker, reset your Google Chrome browser settings. Click the Chrome menu icon (at the top right corner of Google Chrome) and select Settings. Scroll down to the bottom of the screen. Click the Advanced… link.
After scrolling to the bottom of the screen, click the Reset (Restore settings to their original defaults) button.
In the opened window, confirm that you wish to reset Google Chrome settings to default by clicking the Reset button.
Remove malicious extensions from Mozilla Firefox:
Click the Firefox menu (at the top right corner of the main window), select "Add-ons and themes". Click "Extensions", in the opened window locate "Fresh Fruit Search", as well as all recently-installed suspicious extensions, click on the three dots and then click "Remove".
Change your homepage:
To reset your homepage, click the Firefox menu (at the top right corner of the main window), then select "Settings", in the opened window disable "Fresh Fruit Search", remove hxxp://freshfruittab.com and enter your preferred domain, which will open each time you start Mozilla Firefox.
Change your default search engine:
In the URL address bar, type "about:config" and press Enter. Click "Accept the Risk and Continue".
In the search filter at the top, type: "extensionControlled". Set both results to "false" by either double-clicking each entry or clicking the button.
Optional method:
Computer users who have problems with fruit search browser hijacker removal can reset their Mozilla Firefox settings.
Open Mozilla Firefox, at the top right corner of the main window, click the Firefox menu, in the opened menu, click Help.
Select Troubleshooting Information.
In the opened window, click the Refresh Firefox button.
In the opened window, confirm that you wish to reset Mozilla Firefox settings to default by clicking the Refresh Firefox button.
Remove malicious extensions from Safari:
Make sure your Safari browser is active and click Safari menu, then select Preferences...
In the preferences window select the Extensions tab. Look for any recently installed suspicious extensions and uninstall them.
In the preferences window select General tab and make sure that your homepage is set to a preferred URL, if its altered by a browser hijacker - change it.
In the preferences window select Search tab and make sure that your preferred Internet search engine is selected.
Optional method:
Make sure your Safari browser is active and click on Safari menu. From the drop down menu select Clear History and Website Data...
In the opened window select all history and click the Clear History button.
Remove malicious extensions from Microsoft Edge:
Click the Edge menu icon (at the top right corner of Microsoft Edge), select "Extensions". Locate any recently-installed suspicious browser add-ons, and remove them.
Change your homepage and new tab settings:
Click the Edge menu icon (at the top right corner of Microsoft Edge), select "Settings". In the "On startup" section look for the name of the browser hijacker and click "Disable".
Change your default Internet search engine:
To change your default search engine in Microsoft Edge: Click the Edge menu icon (at the top right corner of Microsoft Edge), select "Privacy and services", scroll to bottom of the page and select "Address bar". In the "Search engines used in address bar" section look for the name of the unwanted Internet search engine, when located click the "Disable" button near it. Alternatively you can click on "Manage search engines", in the opened menu look for unwanted Internet search engine. Click on the puzzle icon near it and select "Disable".
Optional method:
If you continue to have problems with removal of the fruit search browser hijacker, reset your Microsoft Edge browser settings. Click the Edge menu icon (at the top right corner of Microsoft Edge) and select Settings.
In the opened settings menu select Reset settings.
Select Restore settings to their default values. In the opened window, confirm that you wish to reset Microsoft Edge settings to default by clicking the Reset button.
- If this did not help, follow these alternative
[instructions](/how-to-remove-spyware/reset-browser-settings#edge)explaining how to reset the Microsoft Edge browser.
Summary:
A browser hijacker is a type of adware infection that modifies Internet browser settings by assigning the homepage and default Internet search engine settings to some other (unwanted) website URL. Commonly, this type of adware infiltrates operating systems through free software downloads. If your download is managed by a download client, ensure that you decline offers to install advertised toolbars or applications that seek to change your homepage and default Internet search engine settings.

Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)
What is the purpose of forcing users visit freshfruittab.com website?
Forcing users to visit freshfruittab.com generates traffic. Higher traffic numbers can be monetized through advertising and other ways.
Is visiting freshfruittab.com a threat to my privacy?
Freshfruittab.com may track your browsing activity, steal personal information, or expose you to further security risks like malware and phishing attempts. Thus, visiting freshfruittab.com can be a threat to privacy.
How did a browser hijacker infiltrate my computer?
Browser hijackers are often bundled with free or suspicious programs, installed/added when users skip steps without making certain changes during installation. They can also be delivered via deceptive ads, fake updates, or downloads from unofficial sources, including P2P networks and third-party sites.
Will Combo Cleaner help me remove Fresh Fruit Search browser hijacker?
Combo Cleaner will scan your computer and remove browser hijackers. Manual removal may not always work, especially when multiple browser hijackers are added to a browser. In such cases, using tools like Combo Cleaner helps to completely remove all hijackers at once.
